column5: ID of the range request/response pair this packet represents
column10: Responder’s range correction bias (Acquire Bias) in frames
column11: Responder’s range correction bias (LED correction + electrical delay correction) in bins
column12: Distance between the lockspot and the leading edge (in bins)
column17: Time of the entire range handshake
column18: Timestamp of the range (in hardware counts). The hardware counter is a 32-bit counter driven by a continuously running 3.6864 MHz clock. It overflows (wraps around) every 19 min. 25.084 sec. To convert hardware counts to time in microseconds, convert the time in hardware counts (e.g. the difference between two consecutive range timestamps) to a float for accuracy then divide by 3.6864.
